LONE TREE WIND, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Lone Tree Wind, LLC ("Lone Tree") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Lone Tree generating facility ("Lone Tree Facility").
The Lone Tree Facility is a wind generating facility located in Bureau County, Illinois. The Lone Tree Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Commonwealth Edison Company and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Lone Tree's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Lone Tree Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Lone Tree's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Lone Tree shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $383,000.00 The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $31,916.67
